line_1: L — d man, our gentry care as little
line_2: For delvers, ditchers, an' sic cattle;

line_1: And (as you eat but mighty little,
line_2: And seem an arrant Foe to Vittle)

line_1: But when you gather Strength a little,
line_2: Can walk abroad and eat your Vittle?

line_1: Away went Hans: glad? not a little;
line_2: Obey'd the Devil to a Tittle;

line_1: And had (like them) but mighty little
line_2: To say: So squirted out his Spittle.
